ez moves beyond the breakout bands to shed light on how the scene influenced not only the contours of sound and El Paso but the entire topography of punk rock.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aMexican American musicianszTexaszEl Paso. 0aPunk rock musicxPolitical aspectszTexaszEl PasoxHistory. 0aPunk rock musicxSocial aspectszTexaszEl PasoxHistory. 0aPunk rock musiczTexaszEl PasoxHistory and criticism. 0aPunk rock musicianszTexaszEl Paso. 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh  aPunk Rock, 1990s, Music History, Mexican American, Chicanx History, Latinx History, El Paso History, Texas History, Subcultures, Southwest Studies, Popular Music Studies, Communities of Color, American Studies, Latinx Studies, Chicanx Studies, Border Studies, skateboarding, chuco, pachuco.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079783140uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/32864440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477329573423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781477329573/original  a978-3-11-079783-1  University of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles